Text:
@torgman1

Convert to mpeg2 format using Any Video Converter. Burn this mpg file onto a DVD-R disk (avoid DVD+R) using DVD Flick. Do not use computer during the conversion & burn process as these are sensitive and may result in A/V async. The resultant DVD-R will play on any legacy standalone players, cars and TVs.

I have tried and it works like a charm.
